SIMPLE: purpuric
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Purpuric
<hw>Pur*pu"ric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>purpurique</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to purpura.</def>
<rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to or designating, a
nitrogenous acid contained in uric acid. It is not known in the pure
state, but forms well-known purple-red compounds (as murexide), whence
its name.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Purpuric acid</xex> was formerly used to designate
murexan. See <er>Murexan</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Purpurin</ent>⟦br⟧
